Sequencing technology: Sequences were generated on the MGI DNBSEQ-G400 using an ultraplex amplicon approach and PE100 library construction.
Assembly method: Raw sequencing data were filtered using FastP, followed by mapping towards the reference genome. Alignments were trimmed from primer sequence by use of iVar, and Variant Call Files were calculated using Freebayes. Consensus sequences were generated based on major frequency bases. Low coverage areas (<30) were masked to N, and deletions (as defined by variant call) were masked, and then the sequence was collapsed at the point of deletion to keep relative genome coordinates.

Sequencing technology: Sequences were generated on the MGI DNBSEQ-G400 using an ultraplex amplicon approach and PE100 library construction.
Assembly method: Raw sequencing data were filtered using FastP, followed by mapping towards the reference genome. Alignments were trimmed from primer sequence by use of iVar, and Variant Call Files were calculated using Freebayes. Consensus sequences were generated based on major frequency bases. Low coverage areas (<30) were masked to N, and deletions (as defined by variant call) were masked, and then the sequence was collapsed at the point of deletion to keep relative genome coordinates.

Sequencing technology: Sequences were generated on the MGI DNBSEQ-G400 using an ultraplex amplicon approach and PE100 library construction.
Assembly method: Raw sequencing data were filtered using FastP, followed by mapping towards the reference genome. Alignments were trimmed from primer sequence by use of iVar, and Variant Call Files were calculated using Freebayes. Consensus sequences were generated based on major frequency bases. Low coverage areas (<30) were masked to N, and deletions (as defined by variant call) were masked, and then the sequence was collapsed at the point of deletion to keep relative genome coordinates.

Sequencing technology: Sequences were generated on the MGI DNBSEQ-G400 using an ultraplex amplicon approach and PE100 library construction.
Assembly method: Raw sequencing data were filtered using FastP, followed by mapping towards the reference genome. Alignments were trimmed from primer sequence by use of iVar, and Variant Call Files were calculated using Freebayes. Consensus sequences were generated based on major frequency bases. Low coverage areas (<30) were masked to N, and deletions (as defined by variant call) were masked, and then the sequence was collapsed at the point of deletion to keep relative genome coordinates.

Sequencing technology: Sequences were generated on the MGI DNBSEQ-G400 using an ultraplex amplicon approach and PE100 library construction.
Assembly method: Raw sequencing data were filtered using FastP, followed by mapping towards the reference genome. Alignments were trimmed from primer sequence by use of iVar, and Variant Call Files were calculated using Freebayes. Consensus sequences were generated based on major frequency bases. Low coverage areas (<30) were masked to N, and deletions (as defined by variant call) were masked, and then the sequence was collapsed at the point of deletion to keep relative genome coordinates.
